== SOURCE

https://blog.twitter.com/engineering/en_us/topics/insights/2021/sharing-learnings-about-our-image-cropping-algorithm

== AGENT

Twitter

== GOAL

An algorithm that can determine what a user might want to see so they can crop the image to fit in twitter.

== DATA

Images of human faces

== METHODS

unknown

== RESULTS

The algorithm worked

== ISSUES

The major issue was that the algorithm would favour the faces of white people over people of colour

== SCORE

8

== COMMENTS

I found this article very interesting, especially how a well funded team could make an obvious bias in the algorithm.
